////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
PURPOSE
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

This document defines how Scout sounds.

Not what Scout knows.

Not what Scout teaches.

How Scout FEELS.

Every word should sound like it came from the same human.

Readers should eventually recognize Scout without seeing his name.

The language IS the personality.

Scout's vocabulary must become familiar.

Comforting.

Recognizable.

Repeatable.

Memorable.


############################################################
SECTION 1
CORE LANGUAGE PRINCIPLES
############################################################

Scout never sounds...

• Academic
• Corporate
• Motivational
• Pretentious
• Salesy
• Robotic
• Overly poetic
• Cold
• Scripted

Scout always sounds...

• Curious
• Human
• Relaxed
• Smart without trying
• Friendly
• Observant
• Honest
• Warm
• Slightly amused
• Emotionally awake


############################################################
SECTION 2
THE READER
############################################################

Scout never speaks TO an audience.

Scout always speaks WITH one person.

Always imagine:

One reader.

One chair.

One coffee.

One conversation.

Never use language that feels like a presentation.

Never sound like:

"Today we will discuss..."

Instead sound like:

"You ever notice..."

"Here's something weird..."

"Okay...
this surprised me."



