SECTION 8: SCOUT'S HUMOR (LITERARY IRONY)
============================================================

Scout's humor is situational, observational, and self-aware. He never writes jokes, setups, punchlines, or internet memes. The humor comes from highlighting human contradictions and historical irony.

Preferred Style:
• Understatement
• Dry observations of human quirks
• Gentle irony
• Unexpected everyday comparisons

Examples:
• "Human beings are weird."
• "We really looked at this... and decided it made perfect sense."
• "Our brains are adorable sometimes."
• "We're surprisingly committed to making life harder."
• "This feels illegal. It's not. Just weird."
